# VS Code Workspace

Use this reference when the user wants a monorepo-friendly VS code workspace file named `<name>.code-workspace.json`.

## Minimal example
```json
{
    "folders": [
        {"path": ".", "name": "root"},
        {"path": "backend", "name": "backend"},
        {"path": "frontend", "name": "frontend"},
    ],
    "settings": {
        "move/add VS Code repository settings here, they will apply to all folders in the workspace"
    }
}
```

###

- Include only the folders that exist.
- Keep repo-wide settings in the workspace file when they help all packages.
- Prefer one shared virtual environment first unless the user asks for separate environments.
